esidents of Israel\">ninth<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/President_of_Israel\" title=\"President of Israel\">President of Israel<\/a> from 2007 to 2014. Peres served twice as the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Prime_Minister_of_Israel\" title=\"Prime Minister of Israel\">Prime Minister of Israel<\/a> and twice as <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Acting_Prime_Minister\" title=\"Acting Prime Minister\">Interim Prime Minister<\/a>, and he was a member of 12 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Cabinet_of_Israel\" title=\"Cabinet of Israel\">cabinets<\/a> in a political career spanning over 66 years.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Shimon_Peres#cite_note-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Peres was elected to the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Knesset\" title=\"Knesset\">Knesset<\/a> in November 1959 and, except for a three-month-long hiatus in early 2006, served continuously until 2007, when he became President.<\/p><p>He held several diplomatic and military positions during and directly after <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/1948_Arab%E2%80%93Israeli_War\" title=\"1948 Arab\u2013Israeli War\">Israel's War of Independence<\/a>. His first high-level government position was as Deputy Director-General of Defense in 1952, and Director-General from 1953 until 1959.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Nobel_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Shimon_Peres#cite_note-Nobel-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> During his career, he has represented five political parties in the Knesset: <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Mapai\" title=\"Mapai\">Mapai<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Rafi_(political_party)\" title=\"Rafi (political party)\">Rafi<\/a>, the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Alignment_(political_party)\" title=\"Alignment (political party)\">Alignment<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Labor_Party_(Israel)\" title=\"Labor Party (Israel)\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Labor<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Kadima\" title=\"Kadima\">Kadima<\/a>, and has led Alignment and Labor. Peres won the 1994 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Peace_Prize\" title=\"Nobel Peace Prize\">Nobel Peace Prize<\/a> together with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Yitzhak_Rabin\" title=\"Yitzhak Rabin\">Yitzhak Rabin<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Yasser_Arafat\" title=\"Yasser Arafat\">Yasser Arafat<\/a> for the peace talks that he participated in as Israeli Foreign Minister, producing the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Oslo_Accords\" title=\"Oslo Accords\">Oslo Accords<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Nobel_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Shimon_Peres#cite_note-Nobel-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>Peres was nominated in early 2007 by <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Kadima\" title=\"Kadima\">Kadima<\/a> to run in that year's <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Israeli_presidential_election,_2007\" title=\"Israeli presidential election, 2007\">presidential election<\/a>, and was elected by the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Knesset\" title=\"Knesset\">Knesset<\/a> to the presidency on 13 June 2007 and sworn into office on 15 July 2007 for a seven-year term.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Shimon_Peres#cite_note-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-VOA_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Shimon_Peres#cite_note-VOA-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He is the first former Prime Minister to be elected President of Israel. Until his retirement in 2014, he was the world's then oldest head of state.<\/p><p>In 2008, Peres was honorarily appointed Knight Grand Cross of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Order_of_St_Michael_and_St_George\" title=\"Order of St Michael and St George\">Order of St Michael and St George<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Shimon_Peres#cite_note-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Shimon Peres","place_of_birth":"Poland","place_of_death":null,"text":"Shimon Peres ,  born in what was then Poland, now Belarus , Peace, 1994","year":1994.0}